HEADWORD: Cydonin
<hw>Cy*do"nin</hw> <pr>(s?-d?"n?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A peculiar mucilaginous substance extracted from
the seeds of the quince (<spn>Cydonia vulgaris</spn>), and regarded as a
variety of amylose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

